This paper deals with natural language processing and the acquisition of semantic lexical resources, which are topics typically covered in the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The use of web statistics and bootstrapping also suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the extraction of semantic patterns, which is a common task in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of large-scale data and the focus on language interpretation could also potentially fall under the sub-category of Computers and Society (cs.CY).
